\f0\b\fs54 \cf0 Lemon Curd
\b0 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl320\ql\qnatural
\ls6\ilvl0
\f1\b\fs32 \cf0 Yield  
\b0\fs34 Makes enough for eight 4-inch tarts\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl400\sa260\ql\qnatural

\f2\fs50 \cf0 Ingredients\
\pard\tx940\tx1440\pardeftab720\li1440\fi-1440\sl320\sa120\ql\qnatural
\ls7\ilvl1
\f1\fs42 \cf0 		3/4 cup freshly squeezed lemon juice (from about 5 lemons)\
		Zest of 2 lemons\
		2 large eggs\
		7 large egg yolks\
		3/4 cup sugar\
		4 tablespoons unsalted butter\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl320\sa120\ql\qnatural
\ls7\ilvl0\cf0 		\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl400\sa260\ql\qnatural

\f2\fs50 \cf0 Directions\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl320\sa360\ql\qnatural
\ls8\ilvl0
\f1\fs42 \cf0 {\listtext	1.	}Place lemon juice and zest in a small bowl to soften zest, about 10 minutes.\
{\listtext	2.	}Meanwhile, in a nonreactive heatproof bowl, whisk together eggs, egg yolks, and sugar until well combined. Add lemon juice and zest and continue whisking until just combined.\
{\listtext	3.	}Set bowl over (but not touching) simmering water. Continuously stir mixture with a heatproof spatula until mixture has thickened to a pudding-like texture, about 10 minutes.\
{\listtext	4.	}Remove bowl from heat and whisk in butter until melted. Strain mixture through a fine sieve into a large bowl. Cover lemon curd with a sheet of plastic wrap, pressing plastic wrap onto the surface of the lemon curd to prevent a skin from forming.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl480\sa280\ql\qnatural

\f0\b\fs54 \cf0 Amaretto Meringue
\b0 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl320\ql\qnatural
\ls9\ilvl0
\f1\b\fs32 \cf0 Yield  
\b0\fs34 Makes enough for eight 4-inch tarts\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl400\sa260\ql\qnatural

\f2\fs50 \cf0 Ingredients\
\pard\tx940\tx1440\pardeftab720\li1440\fi-1440\sl320\sa120\ql\qnatural
\ls10\ilvl1
\f1\fs42 \cf0 		7 large egg whites\
		1 3/4 cups sugar\
		1/2 teaspoon cream of tartar\
		1 tablespoon plus 1 teaspoon amaretto liqueur\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl320\sa120\ql\qnatural
\ls10\ilvl0\cf0 		\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl400\sa260\ql\qnatural

\f2\fs50 \cf0 Directions\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl320\sa360\ql\qnatural
\ls11\ilvl0
\f1\fs42 \cf0 {\listtext	1.	}In the bowl of an electric mixer fitted with the whisk attachment, whisk together egg whites and sugar until combined.\
{\listtext	2.	}Set bowl over (but not touching) simmering water; continue whisking until sugar is completely dissolved and mixture has reached 140 degrees on a instant-read thermometer, 6 to 8 minutes.\
{\listtext	3.	}Return bowl to electric mixer and beat on high speed until thick, about 3 minutes. Add cream of tartar and continue beating until stiff peaks form, about 3 minutes more. Add amaretto liqueur and beat until just combined.\
